1
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:35,070
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:36,990
[Episode 7]

3
00:01:37,110 --> 00:01:39,590
[Model Competition]

4
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,990
Ladies and gentlemen.

5
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:52,340
Mom, you're back.

6
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,350
Let's eat.

7
00:01:53,430 --> 00:01:54,150
Okay.

8
00:01:57,610 --> 00:02:01,070
It seems we've got ourselves a little Cinderella in the house.

9
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:03,480
Here. I didn't use soybean oil to stir-fry it.

10
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,580
I used rapeseed oil.

11
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:06,130
Stir-frying with rapeseed oil makes it more delicious.

12
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:07,730
You've learned well from me.

13
00:02:11,020 --> 00:02:12,550
You're looking at it again.

14
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,680
You really want to be a model?

15
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:20,880
Mom, I also told Siyi about it just now.

16
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,570
If she could also do the shoot,

17
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:24,050
that would be awesome.

18
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:26,860
It's much faster money than working a regular job.

19
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,550
Aren't you worried they might prefer Siyi

20
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:30,610
and eliminate you?

21
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:33,820
That's not likely, is it?

22
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:37,340
Who would choose a Xiali when they could have a Mercedes?

23
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:38,570
Mom!

24
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,290
I was just teasing you.

25
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:43,380
In my heart,

26
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:45,270
my daughter Fenghua is the prettiest.

27
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:46,550
Even prettier than Gong Li or Zhang Ziyi,

28
00:02:46,550 --> 00:02:47,600
or anyone else.

29
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,190
What's wrong?

30
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,079
Are you worried?

31
00:03:02,070 --> 00:03:05,800
If they could only choose one of us for the ad shoot,

32
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,700
I'd rather they choose Siyi.

33
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:09,760
I'm okay with that.

34
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:12,630
Why?

35
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:15,110
I have parents and everything.

36
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:17,070
Siyi needs the money more than I do.

37
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:22,730
What?

38
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:25,040
Is it wrong for me to think this way?

39
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:26,990
No, it's not wrong.

40
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:29,329
If you treat her as a friend,

41
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:31,790
it's right to think of her needs more.

42
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,829
Money-making opportunities,

43
00:03:33,829 --> 00:03:35,360
if lost, can be found again.

44
00:03:37,270 --> 00:03:38,660
But it's just,

45
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:43,600
if one day,

46
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:48,829
you need to give up something else...

47
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,900
Something else? What do you mean by that?

48
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,160
It's nothing.

49
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,000
What is it?

50
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:00,420
Never mind.

51
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,610
Fenghua, are you home?

52
00:04:03,050 --> 00:04:03,810
I'm not!

53
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:13,320
Fenghua.

54
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:17,490
Go away.

55
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,690
Let's talk for a bit.

56
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:20,709
Not available.

57
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:22,730
Come on, just a quick chat.

58
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:25,740
Come on.

59
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:51,000
Alright, who wants to go first?

60
00:04:56,880 --> 00:05:00,320
[Reimbursement Voucher]

61
00:04:58,550 --> 00:04:59,390
What is this?

62
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:05,440
A reimbursement voucher for Chris Lee's concert ticket.

63
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:07,760
What does that mean?

64
00:05:07,970 --> 00:05:09,640
From now on, when you buy concert tickets,

65
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,900
no matter how much they cost,

66
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,100
we'll reimburse you.

67
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:17,750
[Reimbursement Voucher]

68
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:21,020
[To the Future You]

69
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,720
That's not necessary.

70
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,150
I don't need your money.

71
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:31,990
This is our way of showing we care.

72
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,760
Sorry!

73
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:42,640
We were wrong.

74
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,310
Is Chris good?

75
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:54,390
Yes.

76
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:55,670
Does she sing well?

77
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,500
Yes, she does.

78
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,310
If any one of you dares to mess with me again,

79
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:00,950
I...

80
00:06:03,910 --> 00:06:05,840
I'll sneak into your rooms at night

81
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:08,480
and shave all your heads one by one.

82
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,830
Why aren't you dodging?

83
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,600
Why are you laughing?

84
00:06:13,030 --> 00:06:14,630
Don't let this happen again.

85
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,790
Fixed that. Let's go.

86
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,950
What's got you so happy?

87
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:27,910
Nothing.

88
00:06:56,690 --> 00:06:57,500
Cheers.

89
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,120
Alright.

90
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,350
The other day,

91
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,770
I ran into Siyi at the hospital. She was going to tutor Chen Rui.

92
00:07:19,470 --> 00:07:20,710
Well,

93
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:21,980
I don't know what I was thinking.

94
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:23,350
I... I just

95
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:26,030
blurted out to Siyi,

96
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,610
"Why don't you come stay at our place?"

97
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:36,230
You invited Siyi to live with us?

98
00:07:36,350 --> 00:07:37,950
Are you trying to kick me out?

99
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:39,720
Or are you

100
00:07:39,740 --> 00:07:42,150
trying to create an opportunity for her and our son?

101
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,350
No, it's not like that.

102
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:45,350
I only did that for our son's studies.

103
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:47,990
His tutoring while in the hospital is the most important thing right now.

104
00:07:47,990 --> 00:07:49,590
That girl has been helping Chen Rui.

105
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:51,600
And I thought since she's going through a lot,

106
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,130
I wanted to help her out too.

107
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:54,230
After all, I have a car.

108
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:55,870
Stop, just stop.

109
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:57,390
You're meddling too much.

110
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:59,670
Our son has complained to me many times in private,

111
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:01,160
saying you meddle in everything,

112
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,030
from his studies,

113
00:08:02,030 --> 00:08:03,590
his life, to his friendships.

114
00:08:03,590 --> 00:08:04,460
He's fed up with it.

115
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:06,660
Boys need to be given more freedom, you know?

116
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:07,590
If I don't take care of those things, who will?

117
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:08,720
I'm his mother.

118
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,600
And speaking of his friendships,

119
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,670
just look at those friends he made,

120
00:08:10,670 --> 00:08:11,710
like Xie Wanghe.

121
00:08:11,710 --> 00:08:13,290
Is there even one good student among them?

122
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:15,730
They'll all have a bad influence on him.

123
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:18,470
Poor grades don't mean they're bad people.

124
00:08:18,470 --> 00:08:19,230
That's a different matter.

125
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:21,900
We are all neighbors. We know each other very well.

126
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:23,890
Besides, Ma Siyi

127
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,540
hangs out with them every day.

128
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:27,150
It hasn't affected her studies.

129
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:28,350
She got into the same school as our son,

130
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:28,710
No. 1 High School, right?

131
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,080
Oh, please.

132
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,669
Can't you tell your son's got a crush

133
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:33,730
on Ma Siyi?

134
00:08:34,289 --> 00:08:35,270
I can.

135
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:36,150
So what?

136
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:39,030
"So what?" Let me tell you.

137
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:41,260
This little spark of our son's puppy love

138
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:43,140
must be strangled at birth.

139
00:08:43,179 --> 00:08:44,440
It's non-negotiable.

140
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:49,400
You're too cold-hearted.

141
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,540
You know what?

142
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,150
I was also

143
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,250
once our son's age.

144
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:56,600
It's normal for a boy to like a girl.

145
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:57,770
As the ancients said,

146
00:08:57,770 --> 00:08:58,910
"A beautiful and virtuous woman

147
00:08:58,910 --> 00:08:59,790
is what a gentleman pursues."

148
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:00,910
Back in my day...

149
00:09:07,060 --> 00:09:08,790
What happened back in your day?

150
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:11,900
Back in my day...

151
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,890
Which year do you mean exactly?

152
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:15,920
And who's in that story?

153
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:18,750
Why haven't you ever told me about this?

154
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:22,610
Back in my day,

155
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:26,670
I didn't have the chance for puppy love.

156
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:30,480
But times are different now.

157
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,710
Our son is at this age when

158
00:09:31,710 --> 00:09:33,910
the more you try to control him, the more he'll rebel, you know?

159
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,730
He'll do the opposite of what you say.

160
00:09:35,730 --> 00:09:37,810
So according to you, I should just leave him alone

161
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:38,620
and let him be?

162
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:40,610
Free to date like you were?

163
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:44,710
You need to use the right approaches and methods.

164
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,390
We should learn wisdom from the ancients.

165
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:47,910
Look at how Yu the Great controlled the floods.

166
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,350
He mainly adopted the method of diversion and channeling instead of...

167
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:51,190
Don't give me that useless talk.

168
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,500
Let me tell you.

169
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:54,030
Regarding our son's puppy love,

170
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,470
you better handle it well.

171
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:57,470
Show me what great wisdom you have.

172
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,680
If you can't handle it properly,

173
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,780
we'll deal with it from the root.

174
00:10:00,810 --> 00:10:02,470
Then you'll have to come clean with me:

175
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:04,430
Who was your puppy love?

176
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:06,030
What's her name?

177
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,410
Where is she now?

178
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:08,910
Are you still in contact?

179
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:10,970
Is our son taking after you?

180
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:15,860
Please rest assured, Boss.

181
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:17,920
I promise I'll complete the mission.

182
00:10:39,710 --> 00:10:40,350
Dad.

183
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:42,860
What's up?

184
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,570
Can you do me a favor?

185
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,910
Go ahead.

186
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:53,730
Could you help me deliver this letter?

187
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:57,900
[To Ma Siyi]

188
00:10:58,780 --> 00:10:59,620
A love letter?

189
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,950
No, it's not.

190
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:01,770
What are you talking about?

191
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:02,870
Don't make wild guesses.

192
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:02,790
[To Ma Siyi]

193
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,200
It's nothing like that.

194
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:07,260
We're just good friends, nothing more.

195
00:11:07,290 --> 00:11:07,990
There's really nothing going on.

196
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:09,630
There's absolutely nothing ambiguous, you know...

197
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:12,030
Alright, forget it. Just give it back to me.

198
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:14,470
It's just the other day,

199
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:16,950
my mom said something inappropriate to her, right?

200
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:18,630
So I thought I'd explain to her.

201
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:19,760
You understand, right?

202
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,020
Why are you so nervous?

203
00:11:22,470 --> 00:11:23,430
I'm not your mom.

204
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:25,000
Yeah, right.

205
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,590
Still...

206
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:26,710
Besides,

207
00:11:27,350 --> 00:11:28,830
even if it is a love letter,

208
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:29,800
so what?

209
00:11:30,780 --> 00:11:33,440
Everyone's written a love letter at some point.

210
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,940
You want to hear my story?

211
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:42,870
I promise I won't tell mom.

212
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,210
When I was in senior high school,

213
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:53,070
there was also

214
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:55,530
a female classmate I was close to.

215
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:59,280
Back then, we also wrote letters often.

216
00:11:59,610 --> 00:12:00,930
Just the stamps alone,

217
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:04,050
I collected enough to fill a small, thick album.

218
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:13,600
So you'll be a second-generation celebrity?

219
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,840
I can't say whether I'll be a second-generation celebrity or not,

220
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:18,570
but I surely will have connections in the entertainment industry.

221
00:12:22,710 --> 00:12:24,150
Isn't that Siyi?

222
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:30,750
Siyi!

223
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:33,270
Stop there!

224
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:35,120
Siyi!

225
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:39,920
What are you doing?

226
00:12:40,310 --> 00:12:41,840
Are you working part-time?

227
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,700
It's none of your business.

228
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:46,130
Does Granny know about this?

229
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:48,530
If you dare to tell her, I won't forgive you.

230
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:49,760
Siyi.

231
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:51,840
How much more money do you need?

232
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,240
We'll make up the difference for you.

233
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:55,120
Go back to school immediately.

234
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:55,950
Do you hear me?

235
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:58,040
You should be the one to go to school and study, okay?

236
00:12:58,040 --> 00:12:59,840
You don't have to worry about me.

237
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,350
I can't get into college, so a degree is enough for me.

238
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:03,360
But you can't do that.

239
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,690
This last year is very important for you.

240
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:05,960
You can't waste a single minute.

241
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,510
Go home!

242
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:08,530
If you don't go home, I'll tell your homeroom teacher.

243
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:09,500
I'll have her contact Granny.

244
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,190
Let go.

245
00:13:10,530 --> 00:13:11,110
Go home!

246
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:12,040
Let go of me!

247
00:13:15,010 --> 00:13:16,540
Can't you just listen to me?

248
00:13:16,710 --> 00:13:17,840
Xie Wanghe!

249
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,170
You may be able to tell me what to do once or twice,

250
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:20,590
but do you think you can do that for the whole life?

251
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:21,230
I can!

252
00:13:31,180 --> 00:13:32,150
I can't.

253
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:40,790
Siyi!

254
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:46,560
So,

255
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,190
in the end, which one of you

256
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:50,920
changed their mind first?

257
00:13:53,530 --> 00:13:55,120
We...

258
00:13:55,650 --> 00:13:56,910
We never confessed our feelings to each other.

259
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:58,210
So...

260
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:01,040
We can't really say who fell out of love first.

261
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:03,270
Why didn't you confess your feelings?

262
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:05,680
How should I put it?

263
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,680
Your generation,

264
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:15,660
when it comes to relationships,

265
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:16,450
it's more...

266
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:17,760
casual.

267
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:20,200
If you like someone, you just get together.

268
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,120
If you don't feel it anymore, you break up.

269
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,190
It was different back in our time.

270
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:25,950
Even if you liked someone,

271
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,900
you had to weigh it carefully in your mind.

272
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,090
Weigh it.

273
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,030
Weigh what?

274
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:35,870
What is it?

275
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:39,080
Whether you can make that person happy or not.

276
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,350
If you like someone,

277
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:42,600
you only need to be thick-skinned

278
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,780
to confess your feelings.

279
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:47,540
But if you truly like someone,

280
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:50,180
you must be clear about

281
00:14:50,210 --> 00:14:52,330
what you can do for that person.

282
00:14:58,180 --> 00:15:00,380
But if there's something I can't do now,

283
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:03,640
it doesn't mean I won't be able to do that in the future, right?

284
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,230
Right.

285
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,340
So if you want to make that person happy,

286
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:09,040
you must do everything you can

287
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,950
to make yourself stand out.

288
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,000
In a responsible relationship,

289
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:16,540
actions speak louder than words.

290
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:19,630
Right now,

291
00:15:19,660 --> 00:15:21,460
you're relying on your parents.

292
00:15:22,620 --> 00:15:24,540
If you can't provide that person

293
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:25,840
with enough support and care

294
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:28,500
on your own,

295
00:15:28,530 --> 00:15:31,060
then it's not the time to be in a relationship.

296
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:49,400
Are you alright?

297
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,930
How are you feeling?

298
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,540
What time is it now?

299
00:16:22,670 --> 00:16:23,750
We have to hurry up.

300
00:16:23,870 --> 00:16:26,130
I still have to meet Jiu for the card game.

301
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:28,680
You're annoying.

302
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:41,510
Crippled Sun!

303
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:45,980
Xie Tiancheng, what are you doing here?

304
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:48,100
If you don't give me the money today,

305
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,270
I'll kill you!

306
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,860
I told you I have no money. Which part of that you don't understand?

307
00:16:55,860 --> 00:16:57,910
No money? You have no money, but you are fooling around with a woman?

308
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:59,150
You even drive a Mercedes.

309
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,510
You've got some nerve, Xie Tiancheng.

310
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,710
You even dare to break in and steal.

311
00:17:10,190 --> 00:17:12,829
Murder! Murder!

312
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:51,950
It's not very serious.

313
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:53,230
Rest more at home.

314
00:17:53,230 --> 00:17:54,390
Keep that in mind, okay?

315
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:55,270
Alright.

316
00:18:07,930 --> 00:18:09,080
Come on, come on.

317
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:09,780
Have a seat.

318
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:10,400
Come on, come on.

319
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,770
Have a seat.

320
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,530
Sit.

321
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,210
What are you looking at?

322
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,310
It doesn't seem

323
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:23,320
like a big deal.

324
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:26,410
I'm fine,

325
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,010
but you're not.

326
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:29,970
Aggravated assault.

327
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,950
That's enough for a few years in prison.

328
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,440
I only kicked you once.

329
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:34,390
You lost your balance.

330
00:18:34,390 --> 00:18:35,060
You fell

331
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,510
and injured yourself.

332
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:37,620
How did that become an aggravated assault?

333
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:39,920
W-What do you mean I did it to myself?

334
00:18:39,950 --> 00:18:42,590
I didn't take these X-rays, did I?

335
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,950
I got seven stitches

336
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:47,090
and a mild concussion.

337
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,440
Let me tell you something.

338
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,980
If I report this to the Public Security Bureau,

339
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:51,620
it would be assault and battery,

340
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:54,080
where the victim doesn't accept mediation.

341
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,940
Think about the consequences yourself.

342
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:01,900
Give me back the money first.

343
00:19:02,190 --> 00:19:03,990
I'll take full responsibility.

344
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:05,120
Taking full responsibility?

345
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:06,710
Can you really handle it?

346
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:07,630
Let me ask you,

347
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:09,230
you hit me first, didn't you?

348
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:11,690
You kicked me, didn't you?

349
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:15,310
You could have sued me

350
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:17,110
for not paying you.

351
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:18,930
Why did you have to use violence?

352
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:19,870
I'm telling you,

353
00:19:19,870 --> 00:19:21,310
if I were less decent,

354
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,790
I could add another charge against you.

355
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:24,430
Burglary.

356
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:26,890
Even if it was just an attempt,

357
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:29,340
that would be enough to convict you.

358
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,480
Xie.

359
00:19:37,390 --> 00:19:39,120
We're both reasonable people,

360
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:41,730
so I won't beat around the bush.

361
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,240
This beating,

362
00:19:45,130 --> 00:19:46,170
to put it bluntly,

363
00:19:47,150 --> 00:19:48,300
I had it coming.

364
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:51,080
The money I owe you,

365
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:53,310
let's consider it as my medical expenses.

366
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:54,040
This matter between us,

367
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,580
let's put an end to it, okay?

368
00:19:56,990 --> 00:19:57,830
What? What?

369
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:59,040
What do you mean put an end to it?

370
00:19:59,040 --> 00:19:59,590
On what grounds?

371
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:00,390
This won't do!

372
00:20:00,470 --> 00:20:01,270
Let's go then.

373
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:01,850
Let's go!

374
00:20:01,870 --> 00:20:02,390
Where are you going?

375
00:20:02,390 --> 00:20:03,250
To the Public Security Bureau.

376
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:03,830
What?

377
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:05,110
To assess injuries and determine sentencing.

378
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,110
Come on, let's go.

379
00:20:08,460 --> 00:20:09,610
You'd better think about

380
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:12,410
where you're going to borrow money for legal fees.

381
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:20,390
You...

382
00:20:20,460 --> 00:20:21,290
What are you doing?

383
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:21,870
You...

384
00:20:21,870 --> 00:20:23,330
Are you going to continue causing harm to me?

385
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:24,340
You, you...

386
00:20:24,370 --> 00:20:25,470
How many stitches did you get?

387
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:26,110
Seven stitches.

388
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:26,550
What?

389
00:20:26,590 --> 00:20:27,640
Are you going to remove them for me now?

390
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,550
Take it.

391
00:20:28,710 --> 00:20:29,590
Take it

392
00:20:29,670 --> 00:20:30,540
and make

393
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:31,470
a cut right here.

394
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:32,540
I'll pay you back those seven stitches.

395
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:33,390
I don't want it.

396
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:34,390
I'll do it myself.

397
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,150
Give it to me!

398
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:37,700
Xie!

399
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:39,690
W-What are you doing?

400
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:43,900
Cripple.

401
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:45,250
I'm begging you one last time.

402
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:47,250
Please give me back that money.

403
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:49,540
That money may seem like a small amount to you,

404
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:50,430
but for me,

405
00:20:50,430 --> 00:20:51,870
it's life-saving money.

406
00:20:51,910 --> 00:20:52,740
Cripple.

407
00:20:52,770 --> 00:20:53,110
Please?

408
00:20:53,110 --> 00:20:54,070
Xie!

409
00:20:54,260 --> 00:20:55,990
I'm a victim too.

410
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:57,040
What did you say?

411
00:20:57,050 --> 00:20:57,930
You're a victim?

412
00:20:57,930 --> 00:20:59,230
I'll be honest with you.

413
00:20:59,230 --> 00:21:00,450
My supplier

414
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:02,650
abandoned his construction project

415
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:04,050
and ran off with the money.

416
00:21:04,050 --> 00:21:06,390
He still owes me the final payment.

417
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,840
My Mercedes

418
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:11,550
will have to be used to pay off debts.

419
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:13,950
It'll be taken away the day after tomorrow.

420
00:21:16,940 --> 00:21:18,040
Xie.

421
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:20,960
If there's no water upstream,

422
00:21:22,170 --> 00:21:24,150
no boat can move.

423
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:54,530
I'm back.

424
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:57,080
Have you had dinner?

425
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:57,640
Yes, I have.

426
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,440
Have you eaten?

427
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,430
Our son wasn't home tonight,

428
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:00,360
so I didn't cook.

429
00:22:00,370 --> 00:22:01,830
I had a bite at Yan's place.

430
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:03,350
About that money...

431
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:50,790
[Galaxy Hotel]

432
00:22:43,430 --> 00:22:46,160
Come on and take a look. Soy milk and fried dough sticks.

433
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,320
Freshly fried dough sticks.

434
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:51,620
Yan, take a rest. Sit down and save some energy.

435
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,870
There's even no place for me to use my energy, you know?

436
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:56,110
We make so many every day,

437
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,280
but we can't sell any of it.

438
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:59,390
Forget about making money. We're just suffering losses.

439
00:22:59,390 --> 00:23:00,960
It will get better.

440
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:03,350
Everything will be fine.

441
00:23:04,370 --> 00:23:06,560
How about I sing a little for you

442
00:23:06,590 --> 00:23:08,570
while there's no one here?

443
00:23:08,630 --> 00:23:09,750
Sure. That's great.

444
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:11,760
It's been so long since I last heard you sing.

445
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:13,550
The 'Amusement park nightmare' again?

446
00:23:13,550 --> 00:23:14,110
Sure.

447
00:23:14,110 --> 00:23:15,350
I love hearing this one.

448
00:23:15,350 --> 00:23:15,990
Alright.

449
00:23:19,190 --> 00:23:24,590
♫Originally♫

450
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:34,190
♫The purple♫

451
00:23:35,230 --> 00:23:45,270
♫And red blossoms bloom everywhere♫

452
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:47,790
♫Everywhere♫

453
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:52,750
Look.

454
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,300
I'm old now.

455
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:58,310
I can't even catch my breath anymore.

456
00:23:58,830 --> 00:24:00,090
It's nice.

457
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:01,660
Take a rest.

458
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:05,390
Could you watch the stall for me for a bit?

459
00:24:05,430 --> 00:24:06,590
I have a pot on the stove at home,

460
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:08,100
simmering some lotus root soup.

461
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:09,510
I'll go back and check on it.

462
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:15,060
[By the Canal]

463
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:11,350
Be careful.

464
00:24:11,380 --> 00:24:12,350
Be careful.

465
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:13,350
Okay, okay.

466
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:15,170
You go.

467
00:24:15,230 --> 00:24:16,790
Go. Don't worry.

468
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:20,200
[Breakfast]

469
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,350
Take a rest at home.

470
00:24:21,350 --> 00:24:22,610
We're here.

471
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:25,750
Let me.

472
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,420
It's okay. Look.

473
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,330
This one's burnt.

474
00:24:30,650 --> 00:24:31,710
What's wrong with Granny?

475
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:33,080
She doesn't look well.

476
00:24:33,830 --> 00:24:34,710
Look at these fried radish cakes.

477
00:24:34,710 --> 00:24:37,040
She put them in and forgot to take them out.

478
00:24:40,170 --> 00:24:41,140
Later,

479
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:42,750
I'll have Wanghe call a traditional Chinese doctor

480
00:24:42,750 --> 00:24:44,030
to check on Granny Ma.

481
00:24:46,430 --> 00:24:47,690
Let me see your tongue.

482
00:24:53,170 --> 00:24:55,100
How have you been sleeping lately?

483
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,840
I've always slept quite well.

484
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:01,310
But recently, in the middle of the night,

485
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:03,570
I'd wake up around three or four o'clock.

486
00:25:03,910 --> 00:25:05,420
Come on, squeeze my hand.

487
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:07,230
Harder.

488
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:09,660
This one.

489
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:15,550
I... I... I...

490
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,860
What's wrong with me?

491
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:20,590
Don't worry. It's nothing serious.

492
00:25:21,140 --> 00:25:22,510
As people get older,

493
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:24,900
some symptoms start to show up.

494
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:26,590
I'll prescribe some medicine for you.

495
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:27,540
Take it for now.

496
00:25:27,540 --> 00:25:28,110
Okay.

497
00:25:28,550 --> 00:25:30,070
As for physical chores around the house,

498
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:31,880
try to do less of them from now on.

499
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:34,620
Alright.

500
00:25:35,150 --> 00:25:36,180
Thank you.

501
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:37,160
You're welcome.

502
00:25:38,950 --> 00:25:40,150
Thank you, Doctor,

503
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:41,510
for coming all this way.

504
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:47,190
How is Granny's condition?

505
00:25:49,870 --> 00:25:51,680
Are you all her relatives?

506
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:52,710
Yes, we all are.

507
00:25:52,730 --> 00:25:54,350
Any immediate family members?

508
00:25:54,350 --> 00:25:56,010
She's our biological Granny.

509
00:25:56,670 --> 00:26:00,190
The elderly lady may have had a cerebrovascular event recently.

510
00:26:00,190 --> 00:26:01,690
In other words, a stroke.

511
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:04,020
If it's severe, it could lead to hemiplegia.

512
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:06,220
At her age, if she has a stroke,

513
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:08,520
it'll be a disaster for the family.

514
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:13,020
You need to keep a close eye on her.

515
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,640
Also, be mentally prepared.

516
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:29,660
You are finally home.

517
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:32,270
Why don't you just live outside? Do you know what time it is?

518
00:26:32,270 --> 00:26:33,400
I had things to do.

519
00:26:34,140 --> 00:26:35,190
What could you possibly have to do?

520
00:26:35,190 --> 00:26:37,110
All you do is eat and mess around.

521
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:39,380
Even the second-generation rich don't waste their time like you do.

522
00:26:39,380 --> 00:26:39,980
Oh, right.

523
00:26:40,230 --> 00:26:42,110
What did the traditional Chinese doctor say?

524
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:43,310
Is Granny Ma alright?

525
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:47,300
Granny Ma...

526
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:49,280
May have a stroke soon.

527
00:26:53,210 --> 00:26:54,450
The doctor said

528
00:26:54,790 --> 00:26:57,070
Granny Ma is showing signs of an impending stroke.

529
00:26:57,070 --> 00:26:58,830
We need to be prepared.

530
00:27:00,110 --> 00:27:00,870
A stroke?

531
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:06,000
That's no small matter.

532
00:27:06,270 --> 00:27:07,470
The doctor suggested

533
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:08,870
we take Granny Ma to the hospital

534
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:10,800
for a comprehensive examination.

535
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:11,530
Yes.

536
00:27:11,820 --> 00:27:12,580
We must do it.

537
00:27:12,610 --> 00:27:14,860
I'll find a way to take her there for the examination.

538
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:15,690
Also, Mom,

539
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:18,920
starting tomorrow, Granny Ma can't work at her stall anymore.

540
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:19,790
She can't overexert herself.

541
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:20,750
And there has to be someone

542
00:27:20,750 --> 00:27:22,210
watching her at all times.

543
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,390
If she really has a stroke

544
00:27:23,390 --> 00:27:24,670
and doesn't receive immediate treatment,

545
00:27:24,670 --> 00:27:26,190
the consequences could be severe.

546
00:27:26,190 --> 00:27:28,650
But with her family's financial situation,

547
00:27:29,030 --> 00:27:31,560
how will they make ends meet without working?

548
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:36,350
I'll figure out a way to handle the money issue.

549
00:27:36,550 --> 00:27:38,080
What are you up to this time?

550
00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:39,510
Mom.

551
00:27:39,550 --> 00:27:40,660
You're not allowed to drop out of school.

552
00:27:40,660 --> 00:27:41,590
I'm telling you again,

553
00:27:41,590 --> 00:27:43,020
I won't allow it.

554
00:27:43,990 --> 00:27:44,790
Your father and I

555
00:27:44,790 --> 00:27:45,590
are still here.

556
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:47,350
It's not your turn to meddle in this.

557
00:27:47,350 --> 00:27:48,670
I'm not dropping out.

558
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:51,340
I'll just apply for a one-year leave of absence.

559
00:27:51,340 --> 00:27:52,310
Once I make enough money...

560
00:27:52,310 --> 00:27:53,360
That's a hard no!

561
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,200
Granny Ma is in a dangerous situation right now.

562
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,350
If anything happens to her,

563
00:27:57,350 --> 00:27:58,510
Siyi will have no way out.

564
00:27:58,510 --> 00:27:59,150
I have to help her.

565
00:27:59,150 --> 00:28:00,310
How are you going to help her?

566
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:02,110
I have many ways to make money.

567
00:28:02,110 --> 00:28:03,680
As long as I have enough startup capital

